The paper focuses on benchmarking reinforcement learning algorithms on physical robots, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning algorithms, specifically reinforcement learning, which falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the sensitivity of hyper-parameters, which is a common topic in control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper uses robots to perform tasks, which may involve computer vision (cs.CV) to perceive the environment.
